From my own experience and what I have read:

Your warder doesn't dual wield until your level 30.
Your pet will never be able to proc the mage-summoned swords so don't bother with those.  You can and should use the mage summoned hands.
I noticed that if you hand your level 22 warder a mage sword it will say that he can't get it to proc. Then if you hand it a mage's hand it will displace the sword and it will begin to proc.

I believe at levels below 30, your best weapon for your warder is a high damage 2hb weapon.  You can also give it 1hb piercing and h2h weapons, but the higher the damage the better. I don't think the delay matters. Or use the mage hands or velium daggers for the proc.

Hope this helps.


